&lt;p&gt;Do you enjoy working on improvement projects with clinical teams?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Do you have experience of teaching and coaching clinical teams in using Quality Improvement methodology to make changes?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has become available to support the Riverside Unit and wider CAMHS teams with the quality improvement project based around achievement of the CQC rating of &#39;good&#39;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder will be experienced in using and teaching recognized Quality improvement methodology and with coaching teams to use this in practice. In addition clear evidence of achieving outcomes in practice.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post will be based initially within the Riverside unit working as an integral member of the project team. The role with also include an element of project management, so evidence of this will be essential. This will be a 12 month secondment until December 2021&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Hannah Bailey, Clinical Lead for Quality Improvement and Patient Experience&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;hannah.bailey3@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
